config VAMS_PCI
	tristate "Virtual Accelerator Management Subsystem PCIe support"
	depends on PCI && PCI_MSI
	help
	  Build the thin host queue and interrupt driver for the VAMS QEMU PCIe
	  endpoint. The driver validates BAR0 and ABI versions, negotiates a DMA
	  mask, owns coherent queues, tracks NOP requests, provides interrupt and
	  polling completion, and registers a versioned misc character device.

config VAMS_PCI_TESTING
	bool "VAMS PCI probe fault-injection controls"
	depends on VAMS_PCI
	help
	  Add module parameters that inject failures after each probe resource
	  acquisition and exercise MSI-X, NOP, and polling paths. This is intended
	  only for disposable test guests. Production builds omit the parameters
	  and their interrupt-forcing behavior. Enable this only in an isolated
	  QEMU guest used by the integration test.
